reviews.review: Just got back from ROS..... so amazing. My only 'flaw' I saw was the first half was edited TOO tightly... so full of action it takes a minute to register and catch up. Its 2 hours 21 minutes.. and the story could EASILY handle 2 hours 40 min and let it breath. Mostly in the first half... it clocks better in the second half. But that's a nitpick.. I'm a old man raised on the original trilogy lol - it still works and I was amazed how good it was. I knew it wouldn't 'suck' - but at the same time I had had no idea this was coming at me. Im at 90% happy... give me 15 minutes more character moments 5 min here 5 min there (PLENTY OF ACTION already LOL) on 4x, bluray or whatever and I'll be at 100% - this is a rare film that gives us TOO much at once. Cant wait to see my second view on Sunday and my 3rd on Wednesday. Is it a flaw to have too much great!!!

Solid effort. No movie with so much lore, backstory, and fanfare will ever be "perfect." This movie felt both original and nostalgic. Familiar and unexpected. Overall it was a good time! No major complaints on my first watch.
Awesome - powerful movie - saw the first when I was 8 - now the last 42 years later - excellent finale -
Fans of Star Wars should love this installment.  It doesn't try to be as serious as other recent installments.  The story moves very quickly at times but is altogether a good ending to the saga.

It seemed very forced. A lot, I mean A LOT of fan service to make up for the disaster that was TLJ. It was a fun movie, but forget about logic even in for a Star Wars movie and you´ll enjoy it. I left the theater dumber than how I entered.
This movie is just a mess. Feels like 2 movies rushed into one. Has no emotional moments and many unrealistic moments. Sad excuse to end the Skywalker saga.
People are gonna hate but if they do they simply won’t ever like another Star Wars movie. This is everything they wanted they just won’t accept it
I found it both thrilling and moving, something I did not say for the last two Saga films. Daisy Ridley is very impressive and carries the film. Adam Driver is also terrific.
Enjoyed this movie, was not a fan of many things that happened in TLJ. Happy with how this ends the trilogy
